While inside I'm fucking freaking the hell out and trying to not have a panic attack in front of her. I'm just super stressed about this and idk what to do. I can barely get out of bed most days. I don't *eat*. How can I take care of everything without her???

Its a mixture of her not wanting to worry me and her simply forgetting about it because her memory is really bad. But today she asked me about it, which is one of the first times shes brought it up to me and I'm just like "It's gonna be OK, the doctors will sort you out."

I can't go back to her being abusive to me. I'll break. It took so long for our relationship to get better and shes not telling me about these things. It took forever for her to tell me she was overly paranoid. I had to find out about the hallucinations from my sister.
If my mother has to go into a psychiatric hospital again, I don't know what to do. I'm gonna spiral so hard and I'm already pretty fucking low down.

brushed it off. But jesus christ I'm scared right now. I cannot go through that again. I am barely holding myself together as it is. I'm on a really bad downspike in my depression and game ending myself doesn't look too bad some days.

but the main point of this thread is. My mums started having hallucinations again. And not just small ones. She is talking to people. And I've started to have hallucinations again too. Noises and things out of the corner of my eye. I brought it up to my doctor and she just

My sister is in college and she's working on becoming a forensic biologist. (wow!) Extremely proud of the both of them. They have both come so far, very young when everything started. 11 and 9. We're all super messed up people but they're both pretty well adjusted.

My relationship is really good with my mum now. I can actually tell her I love her and mean it now. Me and my mum live in the same house, my brother and sister have moved out. My brothers in london working as a delivery boy and going to college.

My mum.. started to get better. By the time me and my brother moved into the shelter it was... like I got my mum back. For the first time in like, 6 years. God this is rough to talk about and this is just the backstory to what I really want to talk about.

But we actually managed to move via a womens shelter, that was super rough because I had to stay with my brother as he wasn't allowed in the shelter because he was too old at that point and I was having to use my benefits to pay for the both of us and it certainly was not enough.

My step-dad left my mum. (When she was extremely mentally ill and had no means of taking care of us and tried to steal away my sister. so.👍) She got even more paranoid. Had to talk her down from thinking there was a chip implanted in her ear that was telling her what to do.

I am a complete fucking mess of a human being, I have severe depression, intense anxiety, a joint issue that causes me a lot of pain and unable to work, on a waiting list to be diagnosed with autism. and honestly probably some PTSD and a whole boatload of trauma.

My mum stayed mentally ill through this whole thing of course, with varying degrees of severity. She was sectioned quite a lot over the years. This period of life lasted from 16 to around.. 21/22. I'm 26 now.

Not until a few years later when it was still happening and everything was STILL escalating did I realize. But at that point there was literally nothing I could do. Just had to... push through it really.

My parents relationship was not good at this point, my step-father was abusive to her and she was abusive right back. Which lead to the both of them being abusive to me and my siblings. At this time I didn't realize it was abuse.

Thankfully I went to the doctor about my depression at this time and whatever meds I got put on seemed to stop them. But I was still extremely paranoid of becoming like my mother who had been involuntarily and voluntarily sectioned multiple times at this point.
then shadow people. One time I hallucinated an art doll turn its head and look at me. I still cannot look at those things without getting freaked out.

She started to have more and more hallucinations, some extremely graphic. The more she got sick, the more team and mental health services were getting involved. Then my own hallucinations started happening. At first it was just things out of the corner of my eye,

At the time I was like 'what. they don't do that.' but she was convinced and she told me to watch her computer. And I sat and waited and she was like "Look there! They edited it!" and I just sat there and was like 'Oh my god. She's snapped.' because nothing had changed.

I think it was something to do with the people we had got away from and she was "supplying the police with evidence". But she was convinced that her messages and everything she was typing down on the computer was getting edited. While she was typing them.

About a year after we moved, my Mum was just getting worse and worse. She's never been the best with technology so she doesn't always understand what can and can't be done with it. I don't remember why she started going on about being in contact with the police,

I was slated to go into one of the top art colleges in the country and I was suddenly ripped away from that. I couldn't even go to my prom because it happened like a week beforehand. Even though I helped fucking design it.

When I was 16, we weren't in the best position. My step-father got in some hot water with some bad dudes and we moved very suddenly to get away from it. We'd been very happy where we were living and it ruined all of our lives in some way.

So. When I was around 16, my mums mental health took a really big turn. She'd always been mentally ill, which put a lot of responsibility onto me because I'm the eldest of my siblings and when my mum wasn't capable I basically became the mum.

gonna have a little bit of a vent thread bc I need to talk about it. so into the twitter void
